00:24:51.950 --> 00:24:52.974
AUDIENCE: Hey.

00:24:52.974 --> 00:24:54.890
I would like to ask your
opinion on something.

00:24:54.890 --> 00:24:56.350
So in the beginning
of your talk,

00:24:56.350 --> 00:25:00.340
you were saying that
humans act through God,

00:25:00.340 --> 00:25:02.630
or Got acts through them
to create a good world,

00:25:02.630 --> 00:25:05.230
and sometimes they
get rebellious,

00:25:05.230 --> 00:25:07.210
and we mess things up.

00:25:07.210 --> 00:25:08.970
So do you think that
in history, there

00:25:08.970 --> 00:25:11.980
have been occasions where
when humans get rebellious

00:25:11.980 --> 00:25:15.980
or when they challenge a
status quo that it actually

00:25:15.980 --> 00:25:17.720
led to a good thing?

00:25:17.720 --> 00:25:19.840
I just moved here
recently from Ireland,

00:25:19.840 --> 00:25:21.910
and Ireland, as
you probably know,

00:25:21.910 --> 00:25:25.660
had a referendum last
week on same-sex marriage.

00:25:25.660 --> 00:25:27.994
So some people would call
that quite rebellious.

00:25:27.994 --> 00:25:30.660
It challenges a lot of things in
the Bible, so I was wondering--

00:25:30.660 --> 00:25:31.380
N. T. WRIGHT: Oh, OK.

00:25:31.380 --> 00:25:33.671
Yeah, I think we're using
rebellious in different ways.

00:25:33.671 --> 00:25:36.930
I was meaning rebelling
against God's will for humans,

00:25:36.930 --> 00:25:39.746
not rebelling against our
societies or whatever.

00:25:39.746 --> 00:25:41.620
AUDIENCE: But that's
rebelling against what's

00:25:41.620 --> 00:25:42.911
written in the Bible, isn't it?

00:25:42.911 --> 00:25:45.540
N. T. WRIGHT: Oh, well, that's
a whole other issue, which

00:25:45.540 --> 00:25:47.905
I'd be quite happy not to
get into today because that's

00:25:47.905 --> 00:25:48.405
just--

00:25:48.405 --> 00:25:49.982
[LAUGHTER]

00:25:49.982 --> 00:25:51.440
We could spend the
whole day on it,

00:25:51.440 --> 00:25:54.890
and it is one of the
buzzy issues right now.

00:25:54.890 --> 00:25:57.340
But there are
differences there as

00:25:57.340 --> 00:26:03.160
to how a civil society
organizes itself in relation

00:26:03.160 --> 00:26:04.942
to what it deems to be wise.

00:26:04.942 --> 00:26:06.400
And from a Christian
point of view,

00:26:06.400 --> 00:26:08.230
many Christian
teachers, including

00:26:08.230 --> 00:26:10.760
most of the Christian
leaders in Ireland itself,

00:26:10.760 --> 00:26:13.140
were saying actually, no,
here's the way we should go.

00:26:13.140 --> 00:26:16.730
And then, 60% of the society
of voted the other way.

00:26:16.730 --> 00:26:19.220
Now, if you live in a
modern, secular democracy,

00:26:19.220 --> 00:26:21.700
that's just likely
to happen, but that's

00:26:21.700 --> 00:26:24.720
just one of 1,000 things.

00:26:24.720 --> 00:26:28.660
For years, centuries,
governments often

00:26:28.660 --> 00:26:31.540
would be Christian
governments-- have legislated

00:26:31.540 --> 00:26:35.960
in favor of, say, slavery, or
in favor of not giving women

00:26:35.960 --> 00:26:37.330
the vote, or whatever.

00:26:37.330 --> 00:26:39.040
And yeah, I think
bad things have

00:26:39.040 --> 00:26:41.350
happened as a result of that,
but it takes a long time.

00:26:41.350 --> 00:26:43.960
That wasn't what I
meant by rebellious.

00:26:43.960 --> 00:26:46.870
Obviously, there might
be specific examples,

00:26:46.870 --> 00:26:50.184
but I meant in the much bigger,
more general sense-- yeah,

00:26:50.184 --> 00:26:52.100
it'll work out in the
particular ones as well.

00:26:52.100 --> 00:26:53.730
In the bigger,
more general sense,

00:26:53.730 --> 00:26:57.460
that there are broadly
pretty obvious ways

00:26:57.460 --> 00:26:58.880
of human flourishing.

00:26:58.880 --> 00:27:01.250
Start with the Ten
Commandments, for start,

00:27:01.250 --> 00:27:03.500
that if you don't steal
and don't commit adultery

00:27:03.500 --> 00:27:06.270
and don't murder et cetera
and honor your parents

00:27:06.270 --> 00:27:08.470
and don't tell lies,
especially on oath,

00:27:08.470 --> 00:27:12.340
then this will be a better
place to live in than if you

00:27:12.340 --> 00:27:14.050
go about doing those things.

00:27:14.050 --> 00:27:18.340
And so as I often say
to people when they say,

00:27:18.340 --> 00:27:19.920
oh, I don't like
the idea of law.

00:27:19.920 --> 00:27:22.680
It's so restrictive, as
though God has given us

00:27:22.680 --> 00:27:24.280
these laws to cramp our style.

00:27:24.280 --> 00:27:26.450
So when you're driving
down the highway,

00:27:26.450 --> 00:27:28.380
actually, it's a very
good thing that we

00:27:28.380 --> 00:27:31.080
know that-- of course, here
you all drive on the right,

00:27:31.080 --> 00:27:34.030
but at home, we drive--
at least we have this law,

00:27:34.030 --> 00:27:37.090
and unless somebody forgets,
we can now all drive

00:27:37.090 --> 00:27:39.150
at a reasonable
speed-- maybe not here,

00:27:39.150 --> 00:27:40.300
because there's so
much traffic, but you

00:27:40.300 --> 00:27:42.050
know what I mean--
because we know which--

00:27:42.050 --> 00:27:44.749
if there was no law about
which side to drive on,

00:27:44.749 --> 00:27:47.040
we wouldn't be able to drive
more than about five miles

00:27:47.040 --> 00:27:49.410
an hour because everyone
would be trying to navigate

00:27:49.410 --> 00:27:50.710
between everyone else.

00:27:50.710 --> 00:27:55.120
So when we rebel against the
broad law which God has given,

00:27:55.120 --> 00:27:58.280
as in the Ten Commandments,
et cetera, then yes,

00:27:58.280 --> 00:28:01.750
society fractures and
deconstructs, and bad things

00:28:01.750 --> 00:28:04.450
happen, and this has
spin-off effects.

00:28:04.450 --> 00:28:07.240
But not being Irish,
apart from [INAUDIBLE],

00:28:07.240 --> 00:28:09.540
I couldn't possibly comment,
though I'd like to--

00:28:09.540 --> 00:28:11.540
but maybe we could have
a quick chat afterwards.

00:28:11.540 --> 00:28:13.050
I'd like to know about that.

